1.5.0 — 2026-07-19

Android Car FM Radio Face — design handoff bundle.

Changelog
---------
1.5.0 (2026-07-19)
  - Design changes (live source + bundle copies re-synced, all 8 reference
    screenshots regenerated at 2×):
    - Removed the "MHz" unit label from the hero readout, preset peek cards,
      out-of-band pill, and nearby-picker rows. FM is always MHz; the label now
      appears ONLY in the tune numpad. Spec §1/§4.2/§6.2/§10 updated.
    - Nearby picker: added a NARROW mode (compact row metrics) for phone-portrait
      and ⅓-slice widths (picker clamped below ~620dp) so the callsign no longer
      wraps and columns don't cram. §6.2 + README row anatomy updated.
    - Portrait/tall status bar restructured: STEREO pill horizontally CENTERED with
      the RDS/HD/TP/AF tell strip centered beneath it and the PTY/genre centered
      below that; signal dB now STACKS below the signal icon. Wide/landscape keep
      the original inline left-cluster layout. §4.1 + CORRECTION-LOOP + README updated.

1.4.0 (2026-07-19)
  - ANDROID §0 (new, top): explicitly BANS scale-to-fit (one fixed canvas
    uniformly scaled). Requires a real responsive dp/sp Compose layout that
    reflows per surface, honors system font-scale, and keeps ≥48dp targets in
    real dp. Reinforced in §10 safety constraints.
  - CORRECTION-LOOP: reference PNGs reframed as per-surface PROPORTIONAL targets,
    not a master canvas to zoom; added self-deception check for a fake
    pixel-match produced by scaling a frozen canvas.
  - LOSSY-ELEMENTS §6: seek digit slide marked required and specified as a single
    two-endpoint transition (enter translateY ±14 / opacity 0.25 → timing to 0/1
    over ~180–220ms), not a keyframe track and not a hard-swap.

1.3.0 (2026-07-18)
  - Documented the hero carousel prev/next SWAP animation as a first-class lossy
    element (LOSSY-ELEMENTS #9) with the exact build procedure: capture slot bounds
    → tune → four 520ms FLIP animations, two easings (cubic translate / quint scale),
    direction semantics, and the resolve-to-0.88-peek-base rule. Added because the
    Android build was hard-cutting the hero instead of morphing it. ANDROID §8 now
    points at #9 and flags it as the most-likely-skipped motion; verify against a
    screen recording, not a still.

